11 SECTION 62. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
12 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW.
13 TRANSFER PROVISION. If the State Forestry Commission determines that
14 temporary firefighters, dispatchers, or pilots are required to meet the
15 demands of a wildfire season, and upon approval of the Chief Fiscal Officer
16 of the State, appropriations may be transferred from either Extra Help or
17 Professional Fees and Services to the proper character code for the
18 employment of such personnel.
19 If the State Forestry Commission determines that the deployment of air
20 tankers for fighting wildfires requires additional Professional Fees and
21 Services, and upon the approval of the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State,
22 excess appropriation in Regular Salaries or Personal Services Matching may be
23 transferred to Professional Fees and Services in the Operations and Forestry
24 - Rural Community Fire Protection - Federal appropriation sections.
25 If the State Forestry Commission determines that the most effective way for
26 it to cooperate in the growing and distribution of forest planting stock is
27 by contracting work with private vendors and/or hiring temporary employees
28 for seasonal work, the Commission is hereby authorized, upon approval by the
29 Chief Fiscal Officer of the State, to transfer the necessary appropriation
30 authorized for Extra Help and Maintenance and General Operation in the
31 Operations and Forestry - Rural Community Fire Protection - Federal
32 appropriation sections.
33 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1, 2024
34 2025 through June 30, 2025 2026.
