10 SECTION 64. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
11 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. CARRY
12 FORWARD. Notwithstanding any law pertaining to the transfer of year-end fund
13 balances or any law to the contrary, any funds up to $500,000 which remain in
14 the Department of Agriculture Fund Account at the end of a fiscal year shall
15 remain in the Department of Agriculture Fund Account and be made available to
16 fund appropriation(s) authorized by law to be made for maintenance and
17 operating costs associated with wildfire suppression, as well as the purchase
18 of fire suppression equipment for the Forestry Division and made payable from
19 the Department of Agriculture Fund Account for the following fiscal year.
20 Any carry forward of unexpended balance of funding up to $500,000 as
21 authorized herein, may be carried forward under the following conditions:
22 (1) Prior to June 30, 2026, the Agency shall by written statement set forth
23 its reason(s) for the need to carry forward said funding to the Department of
24 Finance and Administration Office of Budget;
25 (2) The Department of Finance and Administration Office of Budget shall
26 report to the Arkansas Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee all
27 amounts carried forward by the September Arkansas Legislative Council or
28 Joint Budget Committee meeting which report shall include the name of the
29 Agency, Board, Commission or Institution and the amount of the funding
30 carried forward, from the first fiscal year to the second fiscal year, the
31 program name or line item, the funding source of that appropriation and a
32 copy of the written request set forth in (1) above:
33 (3) Each Agency, Board, Commission or Institution shall provide a written
34 report to the Arkansas Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee
35 containing all information set forth in item (2) above, along with a written
36 statement as so the current status of the project, contract, purpose etc. for
35 03-31-2025 17:32:01 BSS012

As Engrossed: S1/29/25 S3/31/25 SB106
1 which the carry forward was originally requested no later than thirty (30)
2 days prior to the time the Agency, Board, Commission or Institution presents
3 its budget request to the Arkansas Legislative Council/Joint Budget
4 Committee; and
5 (4) Thereupon, the Department of Finance and Administration shall include
6 all information obtained in item (3) above in the budget manuals and/or a
7 statement of noncompliance by the Agency, Board, Commission or Institution.
8 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1, 2025
9 through June 30, 2026.
