27 SECTION 66. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
28 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW.
29 REALLOCATION OF RESOURCES. The Department of Agriculture provides a wide
30 range of services to all Arkansans. The specific service needs, along with
31 staffing required to meet them, can vary significantly due to factors such as
32 natural disasters, changing federal mandates, and job market variations like
33 wildland firefighters, dispatchers, foresters, engineers, and
34 microbiologists' shortages. These factors make it challenging for the
35 Department to accurately predict the exact needs for positions across its
36 different appropriations throughout any fiscal year. To respond swiftly to
36 03-31-2025 17:32:01 BSS012

As Engrossed: S1/29/25 S3/31/25 SB106
1 changing needs and to utilize resources effectively, the Department of
2 Agriculture is authorized to reallocate resources as necessary. Upon
3 determining that a reallocation is essential for the efficient and effective
4 operation of the department, the Secretary of the Department of Agriculture,
5 with the approval of the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State and Legislative
6 Council or the Joint Budget Committee, if meeting in Legislative Session, may
7 request to transfer positions between existing business areas of the
8 department. Transfer authority shall be limited to no more than 5% of the
9 total authorized department positions in any fiscal year.
10 Determining the maximum number of employees and the maximum amount of
11 appropriation and general revenue funding for a state agency each fiscal year
12 is the prerogative of the General Assembly. This is usually accomplished by
13 delineating such maximums in the appropriation act(s) for a state agency and
14 the general revenue allocations authorized for each fund and fund account by
15 amendment to the Revenue Stabilization law. Further, the General Assembly has
16 determined that the Department of Agriculture may operate more efficiently if
17 some flexibility is provided to the Department of Agriculture authorizing
18 broad powers under the Reallocation of Resources provisions herein.
19 Therefore, it is both necessary and appropriate that the General Assembly
20 maintain oversight by requiring prior approval of the Legislative Council or
21 Joint Budget Committee as provided by this section. The requirement of
22 approval by the Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee is not a
23 severable part of this section. If the requirement of approval by the
24 Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee is ruled unconstitutional by a
25 court jurisdiction, this entire section is void.
26 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1, 2025,
27 through June 30, 2026.
28
